onary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Geoffrey  , common in the Middle Ages (as reflected in surnames such as <i>Jefferson</i>). This is now the usual spelling of the name both in North America and Britain. Well-known bearers include the novelist and former British politician  Jeffrey Archer  (  b. 1940 ), the British conductor  Jeffrey Tate  (  b. 1943 ), and the American soul singer  Jeffrey Osborne  (  b. 1951 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Jeffry","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Geoffrey  , common in the Middle Ages (as reflected in surnames such as <i>Jefferson</i>). This is now the usual spelling of the name both in North America and Britain. Well-known bearers include the novelist and former British politician  Jeffrey Archer  (  b. 1940 ), the British conductor  Jeffrey Tate  (  b. 1943 ), and the American soul singer  Jeffrey Osborne  (  b. 1951 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":8,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":17,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":62,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wyc